         <abstract id="aspace_f7aebd817848ecbfb28e4a3ea5f670e8">Incoming letters of Nathaniel T. Bacon, largely on financial matters from companies in which Bacon had invested. Principal correspondents include Edmund Jandrier about the production methods of the Solvay Process Company, where Bacon worked as technical expert, and his brother Selden.</abstract>
         <origination label="creator">
            <persname identifier="http://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/no2007147546"
                      rules="aacr"
                      source="naf">
               <part>Bacon, Nathaniel T. (Terry), 1858-1926</part>
            </persname>
         </origination>
    
      </did>
